(366658, 11489, 366655, 'Aquarius', 2223, '', 1369403326, '[QUOTE=DrSmiley;366655]\n\nNext thing im looking at is CZ different models. PO1, PO7, Duty etc is confusing.\nAnd as most people suggest the PO1. Can i install nightsights with it without having to do any modification?[/QUOTE]\nBro don''t confuse yourself.. CZ P01 is the model approved by Nato and is an excellent handgun for carry & SD/HD.. its frame is made of Alloy (not polymer).. and yes you can install nightsights on it.\nCZ P07 Duty on the other hand is a polymer framed handgun & is little lighter than P01.. its also good for carry + HD.\n\nWhat SIGlock bro meant was that he does''nt trust polymer handguns whether its CZ or Taurus (so do I).. in polymers only Glocks & HK can be trusted.', 1, 0, '182.185.117.87', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
