(370011, 11564, 369844, 'Hunting_Gem', 7161, '', 1370838781, '[QUOTE=nacfpak;369844]imho rangers r to be blamed for the killing of chinkaras/nilgais/black bucks in border areas till close to extinction.i know all that happens there infact my own friends in army r biggest poachers and r the reason animals have been wiped out or took safe haven in india.[/QUOTE]\n\nWhat I have seen in broder areas is pretty close to your observation bro, rangers are the supreme autjority in these territories and without their permission you won''t be able to get a sparrow over there, forget big games like deer & chinkara hunting. And they often seem to be doing it for the sake of recommendations for hunting parties received by their close friends or colleagues and for gifts (sometimes fruits, sweets etc).', 1, 1, '61.5.152.186', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
